-->>Sorting for the sets can be done using the TreeSet
-->>for reverse Sorting use the Comparator
ex:- TreeSet<Integer>set=new TreeSet<Comparator.reverseOrder());

-->>for Maps use TreeMap for the ascending sorting( sorting based on the keys )
-->>for reverse sorting base on keys use the Comparator
ex:-  TreeMap<Integer,Integer>hash=new HashMap<>(Comparator,.reverseOrder());

-->> for sorting TreeMap based on the values
-->>  import all the keys value pair in the list and then use comparator
ex:-Collections.sort(LL,Comparator.comparingIn(list->list.get(1)));
-->>This will sort in the ascending order of the values

-->> if you want the custom sorting then use the hashmap and the store in the list of pair class
and the store the list it in the linkedHashMap which could be used further